  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT253-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">piriviṭait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttatu(C1: varavuṟuttatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante encouraging in the time of separation. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT253">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> kēḷā rākuvar tōḻi kēṭpiṉ</l>
          <l> viḻumitu kaḻiva tāyiṉu nekiḻnūṟ</l>
          <l> pūccē raṇaiyiṟ peruṅkaviṉ ṟolaintaniṉ</l>
          <l> ṉāṭṭuyar kēṭpi ṉīṭalar mātō</l>
          <l> volikaḻai nivanta vōṅkumalai cāraṟ</l>
          <l> pulipukā vuṟutta pulavunāṟu kallaḷai</l>
          <l> yāṟuceṉ mākkaḷ cēkkuṅ</l>
          <l> kōṭuyar piṟaṅkaṉ malaiyiṟan tōrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>He will not have heard [it] , friend. If he hears [it],</l>
          <l rend="indent2">even if something excellent passes by,</l>
          <l>will he really delay further, if he hears of your daily misery,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">great beauty lost on the common bed, a flower on a thread,</l>
          <l rend="indent8">wasting away </l>
          <l>– he who traversed the mountains, glistening high on the peaks,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where people going [their] way rest</l>
          <l rend="indent2">in stony holes smelling of the flesh the tiger has stored for food</l>
          <l rend="indent4">on the high mountain slope</l>
          <l rend="indent6">where sounding bamboo has grown high?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
